More evidence Obamacare is working: Gallup finds number of US uninsured dropping
The number of uninsured Americans plummeted to the lowest rate since 2008 after the launch of Obamacare's marketplaces,  . The uninsured rate among US adults dropped from 18 percent in the third quarter of 2013 to 15.6 percent in the first quarter of 2014. And the uninsured rate dropped by 3.2 percentage points among lower-income Americans and 3.3 percentage points for blacks, the survey found. The drop applied to all age groups as well. Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 